4.0 of 5 bubbles
Still beautiful despite the garbage
Apr 2019 ‚Ä¢ Solo
Like so many other tourists doing the standard itinerary of Vietnam, I did a 2 day Halong Bay cruise with Le Theatre Cruises. The scenery is beautiful, despite the fact that the weather was clouded over and grey. My biggest disappointment however, was all the garbage that was floating in the bay. When our group went kayaking, some of us picked up the garbage on the way and came back with virtually full kayaks - with everything from rusted fishing nets, blocks of disintegrating Styrofoam, and, of course, the ubiquitous plastic items. The bay itself is becoming very crowded with cruise ships, and if the problem of throwing garbage into the bay is not addressed, I don‚Äôt think it will be as wonderful a tourist experience anymore.
On the plus side, the virtually new cruise ship that I was on from Le Theatre Cruises was gorgeous. The decor is reminiscent of a high end ocean liner and everything is five-star here. The rooms are beautifully outfitted with a large bathroom and balcony, the staff is exceptional - from the waiters to the spa service - and the food was among the best I had during my entire time in Vietnam. It‚Äôs just a shame that most of the cruises on Halong Bay are only one night because I would have loved to have stayed on this ship.
Written April 8, 2019
