Be careful : do not book Halong Bay Cruise with Mr Lap
Oct 2018 ‚Ä¢ Couples
We booked a private 2 days/1 night cruise with Mr Lap (hoanglaphp@gmail.com and Facebook Lap Hoang Cat Ba) on the recommendation of friends. We were promised a boat with 3 members of staff to cruise around Halong Bay, La Han Bay and some quieter areas in the eastern side of the bay. When we arrived the boat was different than the one on the photo sent by Mr Lap. We followed the boats doing a 1-day tour and at 4pm we were asked to change boat. Here the captain was not understanding a word of English and did‚Äôt know what to do so we had to call Mr Lap who spoke with him. The boat was unfit to sail, tatty with no running water (or shower), no electricity and actually unsafe (broken bench on edge of the boat, broken glass windows and doors). At the time to go to bed (no bedroom but on side bed in the cabin), we saw a rat on the other bed! At 2am we got awaken by the rat on our bed and decided to sleep outside on the upper deck. The next day we were told that we wouldn‚Äôt cruise and would only go to Monkey island on the way back to Cat Ba (which we had done the day before)! Mr Lap didn‚Äôt want to hear anything when we got back and behaved like a baby, running away on his scooter. We tried to get some money back but he never replied to any of our messages. We want to warn other travelers to NOT BOOK WITH MR LAP .
