Terrible experience with Mr. Lap
Feb 2018 ‚Ä¢ Family
Switch and bait, and worse‚Ä¶ We booked a private 3D/2N boat tour of Halong Bay/ Lan Ha Bay with Mr. Lap Hoang (Facebook: Lap Hoang Cat Ba) on the recommendation of a fellow traveler. Unfortunately here is what happened. Mr. Lap sent us photos of a boat. When we arrived, it wasn‚Äôt the same boat. The captain and cook spoke very limited English or French. Therefore, instructions on where to kayak was minimal and unclear. Mr. Lap described an itinerary so we would stay in Halong Bay the second night; however, by the afternoon of the second day, the captain was already returning back to return our kayaks (against our agreement that we could kayak whenever we wanted for all 3 days) and we were only 30 minutes from Cat Ba Town. Supposedly he intended for us to stay the night close by and we were to spend the 3rd day (until 3PM) back in day tripper territory, only visiting Monkey Island apparently. When we found out after lunch on the second day that this would happen, we called Mr. Lap, who seemed to say that he had arranged so many different groups that he couldn‚Äôt keep track of who wanted what itinerary. We went back to Cat Ba Town with the captain (so it became a 2D/1N tour). Mr. Lap refunded us part of the money (not enough), and also kept the bus money we gave him instead of booking the return bus ride. We want to warn other travelers against booking with Mr. Lap. Perhaps, in the past, this kind of ‚Äòshortened‚Äô tour happened because travelers didn‚Äôt know where they were, but with GPS on our phone, we had evidence what happened and how we were swindled.
